What would be the best way to clean up my installation state since the refresh is not available?

title: Instagram Video Downloader: The Easiest Way to Save Instagram Videos Online
content:
Instagram has become one of the most popular social media platforms in the world, with millions of users sharing videos, reels, and stories every day. Whether itâ€™s an inspirational video, a funny reel, a travel vlog, or an educational clip, many users want to save Instagram videos to their devices for later viewing. However, Instagram does not offer an official download option. This is where an Instagram Video Downloader becomes incredibly useful.

An Instagram Video Downloader is an online tool that allows users to save Instagram videos quickly and easily. With just a copied link, you can download any public video directly to your smartphone or computer. These tools are simple to use, free, and require no login, making them extremely user-friendly for everyone.

How Instagram Video Downloaders Work

Using an Instagram Video Downloader is incredibly straightforward:

Open Instagram and find the video you want to download.

Tap the three dots and select Copy Link.

Go to any reliable Instagram Video Downloader website.

Paste the copied link into the downloader.

Click the Download button and save the video to your device.

Within a few seconds, your video is ready to watch offline, share, or save for future use.

Why Use an Instagram Video Downloader? 1. Save Videos for Offline Viewing

Sometimes videos are too useful or entertaining to lose in your feed. By downloading them, you can watch them anytime without needing an internet connection.

2. Rewatch Educational or Tutorial Content

Many creators share tutorials, motivational clips, and valuable information. Downloading these videos helps you access them easily whenever needed.

3. Keep Inspiring or Creative Content

If you are a content creator, you may want to keep certain videos as references or inspirations for your own work.

4. Share Videos with Friends and Family

Instead of sending links, sending the actual video file is often more convenient and accessible.

5. No Need for Any App or Login

Most Instagram video downloaders are web-based tools. You donâ€™t need to download an app or log in with your Instagram credentials, which makes the process safe and hassle-free.

Key Features of a Good Instagram Video Downloader

A high-quality Instagram video downloader should offer:

Fast downloading speed

High-quality video output (HD)

Support for reels, stories, IGTV, and posts

No login requirement

Free usage

Compatibility with all devices (Android, iOS, PC)

These features ensure a smooth and secure downloading experience.

Safety Tips While Downloading Instagram Videos

Although Instagram Video Downloaders are generally safe, itâ€™s important to follow some basic precautions:

Only use trusted and well-known downloader websites.

Avoid sites that ask for Instagram login details.

Do not download or share private content without permission.

Always respect copyright and the creatorâ€™s privacy.

Using Instagram videos responsibly helps maintain fair use and avoids any potential copyright issues.

Conclusion

An Instagram Video Downloader is an extremely useful tool for anyone who wants to save their favorite videos, reels, or IGTV content from Instagram. It makes downloading easy, fast, and completely free. Whether youâ€™re saving videos for entertainment, inspiration, education, or sharing, these tools provide a reliable solution. Just copy the link, paste it, and download â€” itâ€™s that simple.

title: Difference ESR 115 and 141 with position: fixed
content: Hi, I have an old PC with Win7 and Firefox 115.30.0esr (64-bit) (latest version from 11 november 25) and this website cultuursmakers.be has problems aka differences with Firefox 141.0.3 (of my Android tablet) and other browsers such as Chrome. The green heading block overlaps and hide the upper part of the content block. For example, if you select inloggen (log in), then you see that the user name (naam) is not visible and only the box for the password is shown. Work around: Right click on the header and select Inspect. In the Inspector (html column) select the header tag. In the Inspector (css column) uncheck in the '.header.--fixed' selector the line 'position: fixed;' Now the content block shifts down and all content is visible. Can you verify / fix that? Greetings and TIA, Gerard
creator: gerard32

title: I can't access to Firefox Accounts, Firefox Addons and even Mozilla Support (this webpage) without VPN.
content:
Hi, my location is Venezuela, and seems that I'm being blocked somewhere... I just want to confirm whether this is something on Mozilla's end (considering that their headquarters are in the US), or something on my government's end (since the ISP often blocks websites on orders from the state).

I can't sync my account or log in because of this, and generally, wherever the block comes from, they rarely give any warning. The main page loads normally; it's only the subdomains that are blocked, as far as I can see. For the record, this happens in Firefox for Desktop, and for Android too, wherever I'm on my home, using mobile data or using my office WiFi. This is not a browser error, in the capture u can see that the domains are solved correctly (even using the ISP's DNS), but u can't ping on the IP unless u turn on the VPN.

All Google services work fine for me, and I can't use a VPN all the time, so I'll have to switch to some chromium browser if this goes on too long (even if I don't want to).
